Reproduction. This species has been shown to be oviparous and gonochoristic, but successive hermaphroditism cannot be excluded (
Witte 1996
). Oogenesis takes place between June and August with spermatic cysts found only in August (
Witte, 1996
). Subglobular buds are relatively common in this species, they are often placed at the lower half of the specimens (
Barthel & Tendal 1993
;
Witte 1996
).
